explanation: The solution uses a breadth-first search (BFS) approach to explore all possible sequences of instructions. It maintains a queue of states (position, speed) and a set of visited states to avoid duplicates. The algorithm iteratively explores all possible next states from the current states until it reaches the target position. The use of a queue and a set ensures efficient exploration and avoids redundant computations.

